<It's also in PYTHON..continue at your own risk :) >

--portscan.py is a single process, single threaded application
--portscanThread.py is single process, multi-threaded .....

how to run ?

python <filename>.py <IP address> or <hostname>

(for both the files)
---It will list out all the open ports with the address of each port. 
---for more information about, why the port is open run 'cat /etc/services'





